HEADWORD: Gingham
<hw>Ging"ham</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>guingan</ets>; cf. Jav. <ets>ginggang</ets>; <ets>or perh</ets>.
<ets>fr</ets>. <ets>Guingamp</ets>, in France.]</ety> <def>A kind of
cotton or linen cloth, usually in stripes or checks, the yarn of which
is dyed before it is woven; -- distinguished from printed cotton or
prints.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

